# AI Video Factory — Environment Variables
#
# STATUS: this project reads NO project-specific environment variables.
# There is no dotenv loader anywhere in the code, and nothing reads a .env file.
# You do NOT need to copy this file to .env for the pipeline to work.
#
# What the code actually reads from the environment (verified 2026-07-02 by grepping
# `process.env` / `os.environ` across src/ and scripts/):
#   - process.env.HOME   — TypeScript, in 3 helpers that locate the `uv` binary at
#                          ~/.local/bin/uv (src/pipeline/pipeline.ts, src/pipeline/voices.ts,
#                          src/autoedit/cli.ts). Set by your shell already; you never set it here.
#   - SSL_CERT_FILE / REQUESTS_CA_BUNDLE — Python, read (and set-default) by the optional
#                          background-matting tool src/matting/rvm_matte.py to configure TLS
#                          certs for the model download. Only relevant if you use matting.
#
# There are no secrets in this project and no required API keys — the whole stack is
# free/local (Edge-TTS for voiceover, faster-whisper for transcription, FFmpeg for encoding).
#
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The variables below are NOT implemented. They are aspirational placeholders left from an
# early plan. Nothing in the code reads them today. They are kept commented so a future
# feature could adopt them — but adding one requires wiring an actual reader (and a dotenv
# loader) first.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# NOT IMPLEMENTED — premium/paid alternatives (the project deliberately uses free/local tools):
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=       # would only matter if premium TTS were ever added (it isn't)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=        # would only matter for LLM-assisted editing (not wired)
# DEEPL_API_KEY=            # would only matter for subtitle translation (not wired)
#
# NOT IMPLEMENTED — render/encode tuning (currently hardcoded in the pipeline, not env-driven):
# REMOTION_CONCURRENCY=     # render concurrency is Remotion's default, not read from env
# REMOTION_QUALITY=         # encode quality is set in src/ffmpeg/commands.ts, not from env
# FFMPEG_THREADS=           # ffmpeg thread count is left to ffmpeg's default, not from env
# DEFAULT_VOICE=            # default voice is a CLI flag default (es-MX-JorgeNeural)
# DEFAULT_LANGUAGE=         # default language is a CLI flag default (es)
# OUTPUT_DIR=               # output dir is the --output CLI flag (default ./output)
